title: 2020 United States presidential election in Alaska
deleted: Trump won every pre-election poll conducted in the state, though by varying margins. Many of the polls were in the single digit range, and one on July 7 showed Trump with just a 1% lead. The average of the final three polls showed Trump leading Biden 49% to 42%.<ref>https://uselectionatlas.org/POLLS/PRESIDENT/2020/polls.php?fips=2</ref>

title: 2020 United States presidential election in Alaska
added: Alaska's electorate is aligned with the Republican party due to [[Petroleum in the United States|oil development]] and [[Second Amendment to the United States Constitution|Second Amendment]] issues.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2016-11-06|title=Alaska has a long history of voting strongly Republican for president. Will it continue?|url=https://www.adn.com/politics/2016/11/05/alaska-has-a-long-history-of-voting-republican-in-presidential-elections-will-it-continue-this-year/|access-date=2020-12-14|website=Anchorage Daily News|language=en-US}}</ref>
